New Records: Nestory Irankunda made his debut for the Socceroos.
Ajdin Hrustic scored the opening goal with a deflected shot.
Key Match Events: Ajdin Hrustic scored the first goal in the 29th minute.
Kusini Yengi scored the second goal with a header in the 62nd minute.
Jordy Bos was a standout performer, contributing with his creativity and work rate.
Pre-Game Insights: The match was a dead rubber as Australia had already qualified.
Nestory Irankunda was expected to come off the bench but started instead.
The Socceroos dominated possession but struggled to convert chances.
Post-Match Reflections: Graham Arnold praised the team's resilience despite a challenging match.
The Socceroos expressed frustration with their finishing and the pitch conditions.
Nestory Irankunda and Daniel Arzani showed potential in their debut appearances.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The pitch was waterlogged and in poor condition.
Bangladesh's shot on target was off-target, ending up in the car park.
Jordy Bos was involved in multiple key moments and substitutions.
